    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Halve the <strong>red peppers </strong>and scoop out the seeds with a spoon</p><p>Put the <strong>red pepper halves </strong>into an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> and put into the oven for 12-15 mins or until softened but still holding their shape</p><p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>cucumber</strong> and put into a sieve with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> over a bowl, keeping aside for later</p>",
